        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> For the mob you referenced, AoW, if your mages make mod rods prior to fight and everyone picks them up and drops them by clerics at the start of the fight there should be no reason to make more during fight.  Just before fight melee drop them and during fight the only people to use the dropped ones should be the clerics.  The wizzy's should only be using the one they picked up.  From past exp on that mob two necro's in the group with 4 clerics, the clerics did not run out of mana.  Their hp's also never dropped below 3/4 just using Zevfeers to heal.  Of course this is dependent on how many clerics you have in the CH rotation.  If the number is 9 or higher I know this technique works.  With fewer clerics casting more you would prolly have to have alt healer helping you.</P><P>Personal opinion -- I will never twitch a wizzy again.  A lot of times the only way you are going to get a wizzy to control aggro is by controling his mana supply.  Since the AA hit I have seen wizzys die a lot more than in the past.</P><P>Death to All who oppose<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
