        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=24007&TOPIC_ID=3129&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Necros+in+a+CH+group%2E%2E%2E+serious+discussion+please&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Assuming each cleric has at least 3000 mana, and 6 mod rods per cleric, you can sustain a 3 second CH chain for 1 minute per cleric.  So, 60 people holding pre-made mod rods with 10 clerics will sustain your chain for 10 minutes.</P><P>I think your necros need to put priority one on damage output.  Each necro should be able to sustain at least 60 DPS on the AoW.  That's 107 DPS foregone by the 2 necros doing Mind Wrack & Zevfeers for clerics.  Over 10 minutes that's over 100,000 damage.  If that shortens the fight by only one minute, you've saved the clerics 20 Complete Heals, or 8,000 mana.  Two necros can't pump 8,000 mana into clerics in 10 minutes.  Maybe 6,000 with optimal circumstances, but by that time enough over-agro'd melee will have died that you really needed the DPS and not more healing mana.</P><P>Bottom line is this... don't prop up an inadequate heal chain w/ battle pumping/rods.  Pick your battles based on what your clerics can handle, or recruit clerisc for the battles you want to fight.  </P><P>Cleric pumping is a more efficient version of having rogues bind wound the MT instead of backstabbing.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3707" target="_blank">Brujo Cuatlique</a><br>Warlock, Test Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
