        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> If you have 6 clerics doing a chain against a 1300dps mob, and your MT has 6700 hp, the tank will need a cheal to land on him every 3 seconds.</P><P>That's cutting it pretty tight, means a cleric has to start a cheal every 18 seconds, which only gives an 8 second window to find a mod rod, use it, and retarget the tank. If a cleric dies, that drops the clock to a cheal every 15 seconds.</P><P>You also need to set up your cheal chain to support your *weakest* tank, not your best tank, because if your MT dies (and he will, due to someone lagging), someone else will have to take his place. </P><P>Any tank under 6k hp will need 2.5 second cheals, and 6 clerics just isn't enough to maintain that. ;)</P><P><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
