        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I didn't read the whole thread but here's my take on it. I'll even use last nights AoW as reference. We had a 6-8 cleric CH rotation ( I can't really remember ) but a necro for mana on a CH order is absolutely useless. Honestly, I'm not playing down feeding, I'm telling you it's useless. If you need necro's to feed clerics to keep there mana up you are doing something wrong. Our fight lasted 8 minutes and the 2 officer clerics in channel ended full mana using a 2 second cheal order.</P><P>Repeat after me:</P><P><b>It's all about the god rods... ( Mod rod 2 ).</b></P><P>Hell if you are hard up get a god rod AND a mod rod.</P><P>When we are prepping for AoW we review our numbers, how many tanks we have, how many clerics we have etc... only 3 wars? sounds fun... only 7 clerics? gonna be tight... no mages? lets go find something else to kill. Before the fight have everyone get a rod, when fight starts, drop em. The whole fight mages should be making rods ( and rodding to make more rods ).</P><P>If your raid leader or whatever is telling you your role is to feed, then he's going on a bias of things that have been implanted into people's heads for way to long "necro's are twitch bitches". This is no longer true. Anyways lunch is over, boss creeping~</P><P>Leader of Triton<BR><a href="http://www.tritonguild.com" target="_blank">http://www.tritonguild.com</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
