        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> > when fight starts, drop em.</P><P>Why have people drop at start of fight?</P><P>There's always plenty of rods at the start. It makes more sense, if you can trust your guild to remember to do it, to have them hold on to the rods until the mob is at 50%.</P><P>By that point the bounty of rods has started to lessen because some of them have rotted, clerics need them more because they've been chealing nonstop for 3-5 minutes, and mages are already modding themselves to keep production going.</P><P>Seems to me that hanging onto a modrod for a bit can contribute to a much bigger mid-fight boost than having a heaping pile in the first few seconds.</P><P><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
